Reasoning: The paper discusses task-independent semantic parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The paper also introduces a new target structure-centric parser that uses neural NLP technologies, indicating a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
